                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 20;
                                                  written lines: 20; Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Jonah begins a new column and Amos opens a new leaf. The words and passages omitted by the original scribe supplied in the margin. Indications of the beginning and end of the Haftarot.Some masoretic notes. A vellum piece pasted at the back of the manuscript with a following note: נביאים אחרונים כתיבת יד רבינו תם. </p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
